<subSubSection pageId="245" pageNumber="246" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="245.[151,1437,1045,1540]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[266,486,1369,1396]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" refId="ref368401" refString="Rondani, C. (1857) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: II. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars prima. Oestridae: Syrphfidae [sic!]: Conopidae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 264 pp., 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1857">Rondani (1857: 43)</bibRefCitation>
described both sexes of 
<taxonomicName box="[763,954,1369,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Eristalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saltuum">
<emphasis box="[763,954,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">Eristalis saltuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName box="[1290,1376,1369,1395]" family="Number" pageId="245" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
of or the length of the specimens: “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">
Marem bis obtinui ex alpibus pedemontanis, 
<taxonomicName box="[1043,1085,1406,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Flatidae" genus="Doria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="una">una</taxonomicName>
vice a D. 
<taxonomicName box="[1202,1351,1405,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Truqui" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altera">Truqui altera</taxonomicName>
a Prof. Bellardi. Foeminam a Tiguro D. Bremi misit
</emphasis>
” [I obtained the male twice from the 
<collectingRegion box="[1104,1211,1441,1467]" country="Italy" name="Piemonte" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">Piedmont</collectingRegion>
Alps, once from Dr. Truqui, the second time from Prof. Bellardi. Dr. Bremi sent the female from Tigurum]”. We found 
<specimenCount box="[1318,1436,1477,1503]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246" type="male">three male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[199,297,1514,1540]" pageId="245" pageNumber="246">syntypes</typeStatus>
in this study. The female was not found in this study and is presumed lost.
</paragraph>
